node.text: JC and Henok make time to catch up on their friendship that formed during the first Rate Beer fest and how Omnipollo's intriguing intersection of beer, pop culture and artistic exploration resonates so much with JC. Fast forward today and hear about how @omnipollo beer is available all over the world while at the same time setting down deeper roots in Sweden. We hit refresh on Covered In Puppies, our collaboration DIPA and its drinking beautifully. We miss you Henok & Karl!

Blackberry, plum, and raspberry may seem like an unlikely fruit trio, but they came together to create one of our favorite Daily Servings to date. We knew we'd be revisiting this combination, ultimately pushing the fruit expression even further. 

Tomorrow, we'll kick off a week of fresh releases with Twice the Daily Serving: Blackberry, Plum, and Raspberry! Grab cans for Pickup in Canton, Fenway, and Fort Point, or order them shipped to your door anywhere in MA, DC, KY, NE, NH, PA, and VT.

node.text:
Effervescent, vibrant in fruit flavor, lightly tart, and low in ABV, our lineup of @soakseltzer makes for incredible cocktail components.

Since their launch, we've been experimenting with different combinations, some simple and classic, others daring and novel. We'll be sharing them with you over the coming weeks.

First up: Cucumber Lime Gin Spritz! This one is all about effortless refreshment, combining your favorite dry gin with Lime Soak and a cool cucumber garnish.

Have you made any Soak cocktails at home? If so, we'd love to hear about them.

node.text:
Coconut Cake is the dessert we crave when the weather is hot! The base version was originally released in 2019 and nearly two years later, the Barrel-Aged expression of this Imperial Stout is ready to be enjoyed.

Aged primarily in rum barrels, with a smaller percentage of bourbon barrel-aged components included, the resulting final blend is rich and decadent, yet deceivably drinkable.

Indulgent chocolatier aromas lead the way. Sweet, candied coconut, dense fudge, creamy vanilla, and rum-soaked oak staves make for a complex drinking experience, leaving the senses highly rewarded after each sip.

Bottles of Barrel-Aged Coconut Cake will hit our online store tomorrow at 9 AM for Curbside Pick Up in Canton, Fenway, and Fort Point. $26.05/500ml bottle, limit four bottles per person. Stay tuned for a special UPS Direct announcement coming soon.

Please note: This beer contains nuts.
